{"author":{"id":"d7430dcb1593659e36e48b9a034067765cf9dd501e6326a5992d21aa2aa35bbb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1741363509,"nonce":"LGeIkUoX+ObMOby7pL8ooE+NiQI=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s6tDjIi","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6820","origin":"github"},"title":"Wrapping LEMUR tool for scRNAseq data in Galaxy 🧬","message":"# Wrapping LEMUR for Galaxy\n\nHey everyone,\n\nI’m working on wrapping [LEMUR](https://github.com/const-ae/lemur) for Galaxy with the help of @nilchia . LEMUR (Latent Embedding Multivariate Regression) is a tool designed for analyzing multi-condition single-cell data, providing a flexible framework to model gene expression changes across multiple conditions while accounting for complex dependencies.\n\nThe method is described in detail in the recent paper:  \n📄 **Analysis of multi-condition single-cell data with latent embedding multivariate regression**  \n🔗 [Nature Genetics (2024)](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41588-024-01996-0)\n\n## Galaxy Integration Plan\n\nFor the Galaxy integration, we’re planning to:\n\n- Structure the wrapper so that each required function from the LEMUR package is in a separate XML file within `tools-iuc`\n- Ensure that the tool is easy to use within workflows\n- Handle dependencies appropriately to maintain reproducibility\n- Keep compatibility in mind for future updates\n\nI’m opening this issue to document the progress and share updates as I go.  \nIf you have any thoughts, suggestions, or IUC-specific best practices I should consider, feel free to jump in!\n\n**Cheers,**  \nDiana","files":null}]}